 SUMMARY OF JOB RESPONSIBILITIES 
 
 This position is responsible for building and maintaining relationships with all of the site vendors. 
 Familiar with business continuity planning, implementation, and testing. 
 Have a focus on security awareness and auditing compliance of security policies and procedures. 
 Will need to inspect and review OSHA guidelines. MSDS books must be maintained and updated. 
 Accountable for inventory of site supplies as well as assisting with budget conversations and staying within budget restraints. 
 The position is also responsible for general maintenance to the facility while following general safety principles. 
 Other tasks may be assigned. 
 
 KNOWLEDGE/ABILITIES/SKILLS 
 
 Ability to handle multiple tasks within time constraints. 
 
 Ability and willingness to perform physical activities, including but not limited to lifting (60-80 pounds) and climbing ladders. 
 
 Strong organizational skills 
 
 Ability to communicate effectively with clients, vendors, and other site staff 
 
 Strong knowledge of Microsoft suite. 
 
 EDUCATION 
 
 H.S. Diploma or GED. 
 
 EXPERIENCE TARGET 
 
